Learn more about the academic services provided to you by living on campus.        Bedlofts and Microfridges   Campus Housing partners with Bedloft.com to provide the optional amenities of a microfridge or bedloft. These items can be ordered online and setup in your unit prior to your arrival when ordered early.  Please place your order by July 31 for best pricing and to ensure your items are in your room and assembled by move-in day.       Mail and Packages   Mail is delivered directly to each residence hall where each resident of that building is assigned a personal mailbox. The box number corresponds with the unit number in each hall. You can find your residence hall address on each residence hall page.  Campus Housing will notify you when you receive a package via your UIC email. Your package can then be picked up at the front desk of the residence hall you live in.       ResHall Linens   Looking for a large selection of Twin XL Linens?  At UIC, we partner with OCM to provide the Residence Hall Linens Program .  A large selection of discounted Linen bundles are available at prices that are budget-friendly. Best of all, all products are guaranteed until graduation. Extra-long sheets, extra-long mattress pads, extra-long comforters, pillows, décor and storage solutions and all other products are backed by this guarantee.       Meal Plan   UIC offers all-you-care-to-eat locations with breakfast, lunch, dinner, late night, and weekend brunch dining. All residents who live in Commons West, Courtyard, or James Stukel Towers are required to choose a meal plan.  The most up-to-date information—including an explanation of each meal plan, dining hall locations, hall hours and an FAQ—can be found on the UIC Dining website.  When not using the meal plan, students can pay for meals by using cash, credit cards, or Flames Fare at additional locations on campus including quick-serve restaurants, coffee shops, and convenience stores.  You will choose your meal plan when signing your Housing contract. You can decrease your meal plan within the first two weeks of the semester on the Dock , however, you are also able to increase this amount at any time.  Dragon Dollar$ and Flames Fare are the official campus debit accounts linked to your i-card. Both accounts are available to anyone with a valid i-card‚ including students‚ faculty‚ and staff. Both Dragon Dollar$ and Flames Fare can be used in any of our campus eateries‚ including dining halls‚ convenience stores and fast food.       Laundry   We are happy to offer free washer and dryer use for on-campus residents! We offer LaundryView as a no-cost service to see if laundry machines are available or to alert you to when your laundry is finished.       Technology Access   Every Campus Housing  unit has access to both wired or wireless connections. For more information about getting connected, visit our ResNet page.  Additionally, cable TV is included in your Technology Access Fee and is active at the time of move-in. To see a list of all channels, view our TV Channel List on the Dock .        Work Orders   If you experience any facility issues, broken items, or improperly working features within your living space, maintenance services can be requested entered at any time on the Dock .          Services    Back to main content           Bed Loft / Microfridge    Laundry View    Meal Plans    ResHall Linens                  UIC Logo        Campus Housing         Future    Apply    Housing Rates    Residence Halls    Services    Why Live on Campus      Current    Apply    Summer Housing    Housing During Breaks    Academic Support    Get Involved    Services      GUESTS AND CONFERENCES    Conference Housing    Guest Housing    Intern Housing    Medical Students        Button Menu    Dates to Know    Contact Us    Dock    MyContract    Student Affairs         Contact   818 S. Wolcott Ave., Suite 220, Chicago IL 60612  Phone: 312-355-6300  Fax: 312-355-6304  housing@uic.edu        Social Media Accou